<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
And the Winner Is: Angela Lansbury, star of "Murder, She Wrote," has been named 
"Woman of the Year" in broadcasting by the Hollywood Radio and Television 
Society. Lansbury, who's in her fifth season as mystery writer Jessica Fletcher 
on the hit CBS series, will be honored March 22 at the group's International 
Broadcasting Awards at the Century Plaza Hotel in Century City. The 29th annual 
event also will salute the winning radio and television commercials from more 
than 60 countries. ALEENE MacMINN 
</P>
</TEXT>
