<HEADLINE>
<P>
PAYTON LEADS OREGON STATE TO WIN OVER USC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CORVALLIS, Ore. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gary Payton scored 19 points, handed out 10 assists and had 4 steals Thursday 
night to lead Oregon State to a 64-55 Pacific 10 basketball victory over USC. 
</P>
<P>
The Beavers, 1-2 in the Pac-10 and 8-3 overall, took the lead for good late in 
the first half and held off a second-half USC rally to beat the Trojans for the 
25th time in their last 29 meetings. 
</P>
<P>
USC, 0-2 in the conference and 7-6 for the season, used a trio of 3-pointers by 
Anthony Pendleton to build a 19-12 lead midway through the first half. 
</P>
<P>
But Oregon State, which won its fourth in a row, outscored the visitors 23-9 
the rest of the half to take a 35-28 lead at intermission. Payton had three 
assists, a 3-pointer and a 2-pointer to account for the first 12 points of the 
decisive outburst. 
</P>
<P>
USC rallied within 40-36 on Ronnie Coleman's rebound basket with 15 minutes to 
play. But after both teams went scoreless for more than three minutes, Eric 
Knox hit a 3-pointer to boost the Oregon State lead to 43-36 with 11:51 to 
play. The Trojans never threatened seriously again. 
</P>
<P>
USC had a 37-22 rebound advantage but committed 19 turnovers against the 
Beavers' pressure defense. Oregon State committed 10 turnovers. 
</P>
<P>
Pendleton led the Trojans in scoring with 17 points. Coleman added 15 points 
and 11 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
Will Brantley scored 17 points and Knox 15 for the Beavers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
