WARRIOR CAGERS COLLIDE WITH PASADENA, TOUGHEST SCC OPPONENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The El Camino College men's basketball team will travel to Pasadena City 
College on Saturday to open South Coast Conference play at 7:30 p.m. The 
Warriors are 15-5 after Wednesday's 84-81 victory over Fashion Institute. 
Pasadena (12-4) is thought to be El Camino's toughest SCC opponent. The Lancers 
ended a 10-game winning streak when they fell to Santa Monica in their own 
tournament last month. 
</P>
<P>
The Loyola Marymount women's basketball team will play its third straight road 
game at 1 p.m. Sunday at Wyoming. The Lions were 7-4 after losing at Weber 
State, 83-63, on Tuesday. Sunday's game is Loyola's last non-conference 
contest. They open West Coast Athletic Conference play Jan. 13 at San 
Francisco. 
</P>
<P>
The 11th annual Redondo Beach Super Bowl Sunday 10-K on Jan. 22 will offer 
prize money to the athletic programs of schools that win the centipede race -- 
10 or more runners linked by costume fabric -- and the six-pack competition for 
teams of six runners. Race organizers offered team prize money for the first 
time last year and an El Camino College team won $500 for the track program. 
Team entry information is available at 376-6913. 
