<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOYOLA WOMEN TOPPLE DENVER CAGE CLUB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DENVER 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Loyola Marymount women's basketball team won its second game in three tries 
on a Rocky Mountain road trip, defeating Metropolitan State on Thursday night, 
83-76. 
</P>
<P>
The Lions, 8-4, led at halftime, 45-32, and stretched the lead to 20 points in 
the second half. Guard Lynn Flanagan led the attack with 20 points, hitting 6 
of 10 shots from the field and all 8 free throws. 
</P>
<P>
Forward Regan O'Hara added 8 points, 10 rebounds and 7 assists. Forward Joelle 
Longobardi had 14 points and 7 rebounds and guard Kristen Bruich chipped in 7 
points and 5 assists. 
</P>
<P>
The Lions play at Colorado State tonight and finish their trip Sunday afternoon 
at Wyoming. 
</P>
