<P>
BERNARDI FEELING 'JUST FINE' A DAY AFTER FALL IN HOME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Los Angeles City Councilman Ernani Bernardi said Thursday that he feels "just 
fine" after being hospitalized for a head injury from a fall at his Van Nuys 
home. 
</P>
<P>
Asked if he still plans to run for reelection in April, the northeast San 
Fernando Valley councilman said in a telephone interview from his room at 
Kaiser Permanente Medical Center in Panorama City, "as of now, certainly." 
</P>
<P>
The 77-year-old Bernardi, suffering from a flu-like virus, received five 
stitches to the back of his head Wednesday after collapsing and hitting his 
head on a kitchen cabinet. 
</P>
<P>
He said he expects to stay at the hospital for a few days for tests. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
'Better to Stay' 
</P>
<P>
"I think it's better to stay in here a couple of days to be sure that there are 
no complications, to be sure I am in good shape," said Bernardi, who has gotten 
up and walked around his hospital room. "I hope to be out in a few days." 
</P>
<P>
"There are no indications of major problems," added hospital spokeswoman Karen 
Large. 
</P>
<P>
Bernardi, who has been sick with the virus for several days, said he was in the 
kitchen when he jumped from a stool to answer the phone. 
</P>
<P>
"I fell and apparently hit my head against the sharp edge of a kitchen 
cabinet," he said. "It knocked me out, besides putting a gash in my head." 
</P>
<P>
Bernardi said he is in the hospital's coronary care unit for privacy. 
</P>
<P>
Bernardi is the council dean with 27 years of service. 
</P>
