<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOYOLA MARYMOUNT RECEIVES GRANT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Loyola Marymount University has received its second three-year grant from the 
U.S. Department of Education to train special-education teacher candidates in 
cross-cultural and English as a Second Language strategies. The $225,000 
federal grant will enable the university to provide financial assistance for 
teacher trainees who want to work effectively with ethnic and language minority 
students in special-education programs. For information about these programs 
call 642-2863. 
</P>
</TEXT>
