<HEADLINE>
<P>
PLANE CRASHES NEAR RESORT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By UPI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ASPEN, Colo. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Federal Express cargo plane with two people aboard crashed Thursday on Red 
Mountain east of this ski resort community, but both men survived, officials 
said. Rescue teams used snowmobiles to reach the crash site in a heavily 
timbered area 150 yards below the mountain's summit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
