<HEADLINE>
<P>
STADIUM BACKS OFF ON SMOKING BAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From a Times Staff Writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After listening to pleas from paid tobacco industry lobbyists and smokers 
Thursday, the San Diego Stadium Authority backed off on a proposed smoking ban 
in all stadium seating areas in favor of merely asking smokers to be respectful 
of nonsmokers. 
</P>
<P>
As part of a compromise, a sign will be erected on the Jack Murphy Stadium 
scoreboard that will read: "The Stadium Authority requests if you smoke please 
be considerate of your neighbor." 
</P>
<P>
The wording was worked out in committee meetings with officials of the San 
Diego Chargers and Padres, primary stadium tenants. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
SMOKING; PRODUCT BANS; SAN DIEGO JACK MURPHY STADIUM 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
