<HEADLINE>
<P>
CAPITAL CITIES MAKES A BID FOR SATELLITE MUSIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From States News Service 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Capital Cities/ABC Inc., New York, has acquired the equivalent of a 14.3% stake 
in Satellite Music Network Inc., Dallas, and has made a $5.40-a-share 
acquisition offer to Satellite's board. 
</P>
<P>
According to a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission, Capital 
Cities made an oral bid to Satellite's board and said it has no present 
intention to make a tender offer if the board rejects its $5.40-a-share offer. 
</P>
<P>
Capital Cities bought 230,000 common shares between Oct. 17 and Dec. 5, and 
acquired a warrant for 1 million shares on Dec. 23. It now owns the equivalent 
of 1.4 million shares in the Dallas transmitter of radio programs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
