<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
GARDEN GROVE; 
</P>
<P>
NO-INTEREST LOANS TO REPAIR RENTALS OFFERED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
To encourage owners of rental property to make improvements, the city's Housing 
and Neighborhood Development Department is offering 5-year loans with no 
interest. 
</P>
<P>
The loans, part of Garden Grove's rental-rehabilitation program, can be 
deferred for 5 years with no monthly payments. But the property owner is 
required to match the amount of the loan dollar for dollar. 
</P>
<P>
Typical improvements that qualify for the loans include interior and exterior 
painting, roof and eaves replacement, and electrical and plumbing repairs. A 
city inspection of the property is required before loans are approved, and some 
loans will be given priority based on where the property is located. 
</P>
<P>
More information is available by telephoning the Housing and Neighborhood 
Development Department at (714) 741-5143. 
</P>
</TEXT>
