<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
GARDEN GROVE; 
</P>
<P>
CITY GOES BACK TO OLD AMBULANCE COMPANY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The city is hoping to save a total of $200,000 in ambulance service costs this 
year by again contracting with an Anaheim company that had provided 27 previous 
years of emergency service, Fire Department Capt. Bob Wills said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Wills said that the Southland Ambulance Co., which provided emergency services 
before the city contracted with Medix Ambulance of Tustin last year, will save 
residents money because of lower rates. He said Garden Grove has about 4,500 
emergency service calls annually. 
</P>
</TEXT>
