<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOWELL RESIGNS AFTER 2 SEASONS AS FOOTHILL COACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TOM HAMILTON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jerry Howell has resigned as Foothill High School's football coach after 2 
seasons. 
</P>
<P>
Howell compiled a 9-12 record at Foothill, but led the Knights to the Division 
III playoffs in 1988 with a third-place finish in the Century League. Foothill 
lost in the first round, ending a 5-6 season. 
</P>
<P>
Howell, 43, was hired in June of 1987 from Eastern Oregon State, where he had 
failed to win a football game on the field in 3 years. Eastern Oregon State was 
1-25-3 under Howell, the only victory a 2-0 forfeit by Southern Oregon in 1984. 
</P>
<P>
Howell, who replaced highly successful Ted Mullen at Foothill, was 4-6 in his 
first season, the Knights' first losing season since 1979. 
</P>
<P>
"Jerry came from out of the area and arrived late, so from the start, hiring a 
good staff was a problem," said Jim Ryan, Foothill principal. "He was under 
some pressure, but any coach in Orange County is under pressure when his 
program isn't successful." 
</P>
<P>
Ryan said Howell also resigned his teaching position and the school will begin 
taking applications for coaches with a teaching position available. Howell 
could not be reached for comment. TOM HAMILTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
