<P>
16 MORE POLISH FISHERMEN DEFECT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BOSTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sixteen more Polish fishermen jumped ship and requested political asylum in the 
United States as their vessel refueled outside Boston Harbor, officials said 
today. 
</P>
<P>
It was the second defection of Polish fishermen in the city's harbor in a week 
and the third in a year. The Immigration and Naturalization Service has granted 
visitors' permits to the previous sailors. 
</P>
<P>
The fishermen, all members of the Solidarity union, left their ship, Kantar, in 
two shifts Thursday afternoon. They boarded a fuel barge and were transported 
to a Coast Guard station. Arrangements are being made with local families for 
housing. 
</P>
