<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL; 
</P>
<P>
SOMBER CHRISTMAS FOR ARMENIANS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Armenians in Orange County held a traditional Christmas Mass today, but their 
prayers were for the people of earthquake-ravaged Armenia. 
</P>
<P>
Priests of the Forty Martyrs Armenia Apolistic Church in Santa Ana canceled the 
traditional candlelight procession and afternoon party usually held on this 
day, the day Christmas is traditionally celebrated in Armenia. They instead 
added a Requiem Mass for victims of Armenia's devastating Dec. 7 earthquake. 
</P>
<P>
Hundreds were expected to fill the church hall by the end of the three-hour 
service, which began at 10:30 a.m. "This year we are not happy," church member 
Wartini Jakerian said. "We are praying for our people." 
</P>
</TEXT>
