<TEXT>
<P>
A 46-year-old man was struck and killed Thursday night as he walked across 
South Beach Boulevard in Anaheim. Larry Pughlaska Mandrell of Anaheim was 
struck at 7:24 p.m. in the 200 block by a southbound vehicle, Police Sgt. Frank 
Van De Weerd said. Mandrell was not at an intersection. He suffered massive 
head and chest injuries, and died at 10:30 p.m. at UCI Medical Center in 
Orange. The driver was not cited, but the investigation is continuing, Van De 
Weerd said. 
