IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
EUROPEAN INFLATION RATE RISES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BRUSSELS, Belgium 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Inflation on the consumer level rose in the 12-nation European Economic 
Community during November, the EEC's statistical agency reported Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Eurostat said November consumer prices climbed 4.1% over a year ago and 0.4 
percentage points from October. The agency said the data indicated that 
December inflation would put the rate for the year at 4.2%. 
</P>
<P>
"It confirms the speeding up of inflation, which has been evident since the 
summer of 1988," Eurostat said. 
</P>
<P>
Eurostat said the increase in November was caused by substantial rises in 
Portugal, Italy, Denmark, Greece and Britain. 
</P>
